 Test Audio - Expected Outputs

These are the 3 Hindi audio samples used to test the Transcribe Lambda,
along with what Amazon Transcribe should return for each one.


Sample 1 — recording1.m4a

What was said:
मुझसे हर महीने ₹299 कट रहा है

English translation:
"₹299 is being deducted from me every month"

Expected Transcribe output:
मुझसे हर महीने 299 कट रहा है
Key entities to extract:
- Amount: ₹299
- Frequency: monthly
- Issue type: unauthorized deduction


 Sample 2 — recording2.m4a

What was said:
एयरटेल ने बिना पूछे पैसे काट लिए

English translation:
"Airtel deducted money without asking"

Expected Transcribe output:
एयरटेल ने बिना पूछे पैसे काट लिए

Key entities to extract:
- Company: Airtel
- Issue type: unauthorized charge
- Consent: none given



 Sample 3 — recording3.m4a

What was said:
मेरा फोन बिल में गलत चार्ज दिखा

English translation:
"Wrong charge showed up on my phone bill"

Expected Transcribe output:
मेरा फोन बिल में गलत चार्ज दिखा

Key entities to extract:
- Document: phone bill
- Issue type: incorrect charge
- Evidence: billing statement



 What happens next

Once Transcribe returns the text, the claude-analyzer Lambda takes
these outputs and identifies:
1. Which law was broken (Consumer Protection Act 2019)
2. What legal strategy to follow
3. What evidence gaps exist
